  ldexp
  Builtin Function



      [1mSynopsis[0m
        Multiply floating point number by integral power of 2

      [1mSyntax[0m
        ldexp ( [4mX[24m , [4mEXP[24m )

      [1mDescription[0m
        Ldexp returns a numeric matrix which contains the value(s)
        resulting from the operation:



                          X * 2^EXP





     The dimensions of [4mX[24m and [4mEXP[24m must be the same. Optionally, [4mEXP[24m can
     be a scalar, independent of the size of [4mX[24m.


     [1mSee Also[0m
        frexp





































